  <summary>5/6/1998--Introduced.
International Military Training Accountability Act - Amends the Arms Export Control Act to prohibit the sale, lease, loan, or grant of defense services and training to any foreign country that is prohibited from receiving international military education and training (IMET). Permits a foreign country eligible to receive only expanded IMET to receive defense services and training if it: (1) promotes dialogue between civilians and military officers of the armed forces on the proper role of such forces in a democratic society; or (2) provides for training of civilian officials and military officers on military justice and international human rights standards.</summary>
